Text: 1979 - Pink Floyd - The Wall [Japan 50DP 361-2 2nd Press FLAC]  This is better too

In my opinion better extention at both ends here and the midrange is more open.... Gilmour doesn't sound like he's singing through a tube.  More soundstage depth too....

Listen to the strings just before Gilmour's solo on "Comfortably Numb", they soar here in comparison.

But I guess if you're listening to a tiny MP3 player and ear buds while delivering papers it doesn't really make a difference....
